       <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/lukasjoc/\">LinkedIn</a>\n        <a href=\"https://twitter.com/lukasjoc\">Twitter</a>\n      </p>\n      <p>\n        If you have a cool problem, or want to talk to me then message me\n        <a href=\"https://twitter.com/lukasjoc\">here</a>\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"item\">\n      <h3>What I like to spend my time with (fine not all of my time goes into those things):</h3>\n      <p>\n        A cool problem, Programming, Learning something new, Technology, Bikes, Enduro,\n        Nature (this is biggg)\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"item\">\n      <h3>\n        What I dislike and not spend my time with (ok just a little bit):\n      </h3>\n      <p>\n        frontend development (CSS primarily, also a lot of the JS ecos is really confusing and just bad),\n        scammers, social credit seekers, energy eaters, ads, news, drama, bureaucracy, marketing bullshit\n      </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"item\">\n      <h3>\n        like 95% of my stuff is done with (that is indeed true):\n      </h3>\n      <p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go_(programming_language)\"><u>Go(I just love golang)</u></a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%2B%2B\"><u>C++(Ok not really)</u></a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rust_(programming_language)\"><u>Rust(::ohyea)</u></a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)\"><u>Python(slooow. you slooww)</u></a> or\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nim_(programming_language)\"><u>Nim (is also pretty cool)</u></a>\n        </p><p> Will focus on compiled langs in the future. Think it's just a better concept.</p>\n        <p> Usually writing low level stuff with Rust or Nim, servers, automation and tooling with Go and data heavy\n          projects like ETL processes with Python</p>\n      <p></p>\n    </div>\n\n\t\t<div class=\"item\">\n      <h3>\n        Tools I really really like and use daily (most):\n      </h3>\n      <p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Git\">Git</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vim_(text_editor)\">Vim</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brave_(web_browser)\">Brave Browser</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Docker_%28software%29\">Docker</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bitwarden\">Bitwarden</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MacBook_Pro\">MacBook Pro</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arch_Linux\">Arch Linux</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tmux\">tmux</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flask_(web_framework)\">Flask</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pandas_(software)\">Pandas</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NumPy\">NumPy</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://parceljs.org/\">Parcel(makes js bundling easier, good direction for js ecos)</a>,\n        <a href=\"https://www.wasdkeyboards.com/\">WASD/CODE Keyboards</a>\n\n      </p>\n\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"item\">\n      <h3>What type of developer am I?</h3>\n      <h4>When I design product I:</h4>\n      <p>\n        ... usually try to create a decentralized version instead of a centralized version.\n        An anonymous version indstead of a user login. Lesser amazing features instead of a lot messed up features.\n        <br>\n        <br>\n        ... think of a problem to be solved in the easiest possible way. I do things rather fast and proactive, and yes\n        sure it takes longer that way, but it also makes me happy to learn that way. (Big into learning. love that)\n      </p>\n\n    <div class=\"item\">\n      <h3>Important:</h3>\n      <p>When it becomes work and does not remain learning, it becomes creeping, pressing, bland, unwanted.</p>\n    </div>\n    <br>\n    <br>\n\n    <small>\n      I value privacy and self will so anything you do here is\n      secure. I dont log anything, run analytics or track you. <br><br>\n    </small>\n\n    <footer>\n      <small>\n        <a href=\"https://lukasjoc.com\">lukasjoc</a>, <span class=\"current-year\"></span>\n      </small>\n    </footer>\n\n  </div>\n\n  <br>\n  <br>\n  <br>\n  <br>\n  <br>\n  <br>\n  <br>\n  <div style=\"width:100%;height:0;padding-bottom:100%;position:relative;\">\n    <iframe src=\"https://giphy.com/gifs/dSeVDdzx1kri7GYWJG/html5\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" style=\"position:absolute\" frameBorder=\"0\" class=\"giphy-embed\" allowFullScreen=\"\">\n    </iframe>\n  </div>\n  <div style=\"width:100%;height:0;padding-bottom:100%;position:relative;\">\n    <iframe src=\"https://giphy.com/gifs/3ov9jIoFd00talgv72/html5\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" style=\"position:absolute\" frameBorder=\"0\" class=\"giphy-embed\" allowFullScreen=\"\">\n    </iframe>\n  </div>\n\n\t<div class=\"item\">\n\t\t<h3>Nice to watch</h3>\n\t\t<p>\n\t  <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL0364ACCE6C7E9D8E\">Free to Choose</a>,\n\t\t<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W_o88JGP_sE&list=PLamVddj-8SIlOZ8Cmm9MoPUTv_C5k4JBV&index=3\">Der Alchimist</a>,\n\t\t<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL0364ACCE6C7E9D8E\">Siddhartha</a>,\n\t\t<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bhgFXQIOMTA&list=PLamVddj-8SIlOZ8Cmm9MoPUTv_C5k4JBV&index=4\">Demian</a>,\n\t\t<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rwwQKgq8Mzc&list=PLamVddj-8SIlOZ8Cmm9MoPUTv_C5k4JBV&index=5\">Stunden im Garten </a>,\n\t\t<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rwwQKgq8Mzc&list=PLamVddj-8SIlOZ8Cmm9MoPUTv_C5k4JBV&index=5\">Platon und Nietzsche Un-Zeitgenossen im Gespräch</a>,\n\t\t<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7FeqF1-Z1g0&list=PLamVddj-8SInoTTzOCeygjQ4yb213cWZ2\">Traue keinem Scan, den du nicht selbst gefälscht hast</a>,\n\t\t<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-YpwsdRKt8Q\">SpiegelMining</a>,\n\t\t<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v